    • implementJar

      public void implementJar​(Class<?> aClass, Path path) throws ImplerException
      Method for generate jar file with implemented class

      Implements provided aClass. Creates temporary directory, where .class files will be stored. Compiles classes with compileClass(Class, Path) and creates manifest for jar with createManifest(Class, Path, Path). Delete temporary directory with deleteTmpDirectory(Path, DeleteFileVisitor)

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      aClass - type token to create implementation for.
      path - Path to store jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if implement(Class, Path) error occurred or IOException occurred while creating temporary directory

    • createManifest

      private void createManifest​(Class<?> aClass, Path tmpDir, Path path) throws ImplerException
      Method for creating jar manifest

      Creates manifest with version 1.0 and puts .class files from tmpDir to jar file

      Parameters:
      aClass - super class or interface
      tmpDir - temporary directory where .class files will be stored
      path - provided Path of jar file
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if IOException occurred while writing to jar

    • implement

      public void implement​(Class<?> aClass, Path path) throws ImplerException
      Implementation of Impler.implement(Class, Path).

      Invokes generatePackage(Class), generateClassSignature(Class), generateConstructors(Class), generateMethods(Class) of provided aClass and write generated implementation by BufferedWriter writer in classImplPath

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      aClass - type token to create implementation for.
      path - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if this classPath of token and root is not supported or provided token is not valid

    • findAllMethods

      private void findAllMethods​(Class<?> aClass, Map<CustomMethod,​Method> map)
      Method for finding all distinct abstract and non-final methods of inheritance tree

      Gets all methods of this aClass and its super class with Class.getDeclaredMethods(), Class.getMethods(). Merge found methods in map by key CustomMethod, value Method, and merging biFunction narrowestMethod and recursion.

      Parameters:
      aClass - class
      map - map that contains found methods

    • generateMethods

      private String generateMethods​(Class<?> aClass)
      Method for generating methods of the implementing class

      Finds all abstract methods in inheritance tree with findAllMethods(Class, Map) , leaves all non-final, abstract methods in parent (aClass), than generates methods with generateMethod(Method)

      Parameters:
      aClass - given class
      Returns:
      generated realization for all non-final abstract methods of aClass
